{
  "video_id": "YSVlSmZWzm0",
  "title": "The real reason To Kill A Mockingbird became so famous",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 1540.0,
      "end_time": 2520.0,
      "text": "What if I told you that"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2520.0,
      "end_time": 5080.0,
      "text": "To Kill A Mockingbird is overrated?"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5080.0,
      "end_time": 8440.0,
      "text": "“Can you, uh...can you read and write?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8450.0,
      "end_time": 10250.0,
      "text": "Wait, Atticus, let me explain, let me explain."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10250.0,
      "end_time": 12020.0,
      "text": "What I’m saying is it’s weird how"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 12020.0,
      "end_time": 14200.0,
      "text": "this book is so, so famous."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 14440.0,
      "end_time": 15660.0,
      "text": "Let me tell you a story."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 16280.000000000002,
      "end_time": 18480.0,
      "text": "I read this book for fun in fourth grade."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 18480.0,
      "end_time": 21040.0,
      "text": "I lived in Tennessee, thought it was amazing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 21040.0,
      "end_time": 23620.0,
      "text": "even though I probably didn’t understand it."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 23620.0,
      "end_time": 24520.0,
      "text": "Moved."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 24740.0,
      "end_time": 26080.0,
      "text": "Read it in sixth grade class."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 26520.0,
      "end_time": 27520.0,
      "text": "Moved."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 27540.0,
      "end_time": 28900.0,
      "text": "Read it ninth grade."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 29120.0,
      "end_time": 29840.0,
      "text": "Moved."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 29840.0,
      "end_time": 30780.0,
      "text": "Read it again."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 30780.0,
      "end_time": 31920.0,
      "text": "By the end of school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 31920.0,
      "end_time": 35160.0,
      "text": "I had read this book six times. Six times."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 36500.0,
      "end_time": 38060.0,
      "text": "I personally never read any"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 38060.0,
      "end_time": 39820.0,
      "text": "of these books for school."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 41100.0,
      "end_time": 43940.0,
      "text": "So was To Kill A Mockingbird really 600%"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 43940.0,
      "end_time": 46030.0,
      "text": "better than all of these other books?"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 46030.0,
      "end_time": 49010.0,
      "text": "I think there’s a surprising reason it’s so famous."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 49010.0,
      "end_time": 51190.0,
      "text": "Beyond Atticus Finch being great."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 51190.0,
      "end_time": 53100.0,
      "text": "“I don’t care what the reasons are.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 53100.0,
      "end_time": 53600.0,
      "text": "Please."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 53960.0,
      "end_time": 54780.0,
      "text": "Give me a chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 54940.0,
      "end_time": 57680.0,
      "text": "To understand why this book was a school staple,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 57680.0,
      "end_time": 60040.0,
      "text": "you need to understand other books."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 60040.0,
      "end_time": 64120.0,
      "text": "Like the illicit love in The Hangman’s Whip."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 69380.0,
      "end_time": 71880.0,
      "text": "When Harper Lee got To Kill A Mockingbird"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 71890.0,
      "end_time": 74960.0,
      "text": "published in 1960, she never expected it"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 74960.0,
      "end_time": 76890.0,
      "text": "to be a massive hit."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 76890.0,
      "end_time": 78980.0,
      "text": "As she said in her only radio interview:"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 78980.0,
      "end_time": 82840.0,
      "text": "“My reaction to it was not one of surprise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 82840.0,
      "end_time": 85360.0,
      "text": "it was one of sheer numbness.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 85820.0,
      "end_time": 88640.0,
      "text": "It got a good review in the New York Times"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 88640.0,
      "end_time": 90630.0,
      "text": "(though it earned less coverage than “Ceremony"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 90630.0,
      "end_time": 93140.0,
      "text": "in Lone Tree” by Wright Morris)."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 93880.0,
      "end_time": 97720.0,
      "text": "But let’s be clear: it sold millions of copies in hardback."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 97729.0,
      "end_time": 101810.0,
      "text": "It won the Pulitzer Prize for fiction in 1961."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 101810.0,
      "end_time": 104820.0,
      "text": "The hit movie came out in 1962."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 104820.0,
      "end_time": 107400.0,
      "text": "Here’s Gregory Peck, AKA Atticus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 107400.0,
      "end_time": 109660.0,
      "text": "and Harper Lee, posing as..."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 109660.0,
      "end_time": 112000.0,
      "text": "well, I don’t know why they’re posing like that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 112000.0,
      "end_time": 113160.0,
      "text": "but I like it."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 115920.0,
      "end_time": 117640.0,
      "text": "The movie poster had a big picture"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 117640.0,
      "end_time": 119640.0,
      "text": "of the book on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 119640.0,
      "end_time": 123200.0,
      "text": "So this book was a big critical and popular hit."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 123220.0,
      "end_time": 125260.0,
      "text": "But it didn’t win all of the awards."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 125260.0,
      "end_time": 127400.0,
      "text": "And it wasn't the best selling book of the year."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 128000.0,
      "end_time": 130600.0,
      "text": "So what took it from hit to legend?"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 130609.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132120.0,
      "text": "The most important thing to notice about"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 132120.0,
      "end_time": 135840.0,
      "text": "that 1961 Pulitzer Prize isn’t the prize."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 135840.0,
      "end_time": 137600.0,
      "text": "It’s the year."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 140240.0,
      "end_time": 142780.0,
      "text": "You probably recognize this logo."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 144000.0,
      "end_time": 146080.0,
      "text": "It’s from Penguin Books, and it’s familiar"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 146080.0,
      "end_time": 147680.0,
      "text": "because the company has been around,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 147680.0,
      "end_time": 150180.0,
      "text": "with pretty much the same waddling logo,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 150180.0,
      "end_time": 152180.0,
      "text": "since 1935."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 153760.0,
      "end_time": 156100.0,
      "text": "When Allen Lane founded the UK company,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 156100.0,
      "end_time": 158760.0,
      "text": "paperback books were revolutionary."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 158769.0,
      "end_time": 161360.0,
      "text": "The idea was to print good books, in paperback,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 161360.0,
      "end_time": 163920.0,
      "text": "so they’d be cheaper than hardbacks."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 163920.0,
      "end_time": 166100.0,
      "text": "That revolution quickly spread to America"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 166100.0,
      "end_time": 168580.0,
      "text": "with Pocket Books and other competitors."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 168580.0,
      "end_time": 170280.0,
      "text": "But it wasn’t just about cheap paper"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 170280.0,
      "end_time": 173080.0,
      "text": "and tiny, mass market size books."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 173080.0,
      "end_time": 174779.0,
      "text": "Distribution was key."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 174779.0,
      "end_time": 177200.0,
      "text": "Suddenly, cheap books flooded dime stores,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 177200.0,
      "end_time": 179699.0,
      "text": "newsstands, and gas stations."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 179700.0,
      "end_time": 181280.0,
      "text": "Crime writers like Mickey Spillane"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 181280.0,
      "end_time": 183280.0,
      "text": "became huge stars."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 183280.0,
      "end_time": 184360.0,
      "text": "Just look at this guy."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 184360.0,
      "end_time": 185240.0,
      "text": "He’s an author."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 185240.0,
      "end_time": 187080.0,
      "text": "The books started out seedy."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 187080.0,
      "end_time": 189060.0,
      "text": "Popular Library published stuff like"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 189060.0,
      "end_time": 190940.0,
      "text": "Silence in Court!"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 190940.0,
      "end_time": 192559.0,
      "text": "and Devil Take Her."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 192559.0,
      "end_time": 195180.0,
      "text": "But respectable stuff trickled in too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 195180.0,
      "end_time": 197820.0,
      "text": "occasionally with sexy covers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 197820.0,
      "end_time": 200780.0,
      "text": "like this shirtless Great Gatsby."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 200780.0,
      "end_time": 202180.0,
      "text": "*whistle*"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 202540.0,
      "end_time": 205160.0,
      "text": "Paperbacks became mainstream quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 205169.0,
      "end_time": 207980.0,
      "text": "By 1961, the New York Times was calling it"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 207980.0,
      "end_time": 210110.0,
      "text": "“The Paperback Revolution.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 210110.0,
      "end_time": 211860.0,
      "text": "They said paperbacks weren’t just for"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 211860.0,
      "end_time": 215189.0,
      "text": "“sex, sadism and the smoking gun.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 215189.0,
      "end_time": 218799.0,
      "text": "The books were actually being used...in schools."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 218800.0,
      "end_time": 221140.0,
      "text": "That’s where To Kill A Mockingbird comes in."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 222040.0,
      "end_time": 224020.0,
      "text": "Remember that book, The Hangman’s Whip?"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 224020.0,
      "end_time": 227760.0,
      "text": "Popular Library published that, and in 1962"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 227760.0,
      "end_time": 230060.0,
      "text": "they also put out the mass market paperback"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 230060.0,
      "end_time": 231840.0,
      "text": "for To Kill A Mockingbird."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 231840.0,
      "end_time": 234019.0,
      "text": "Paperbacks were finally coming into their own."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 234019.0,
      "end_time": 236659.0,
      "text": "And To Kill A Mockingbird had perfect timing."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 236659.0,
      "end_time": 238560.0,
      "text": "Teachers had a cheap, popular,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 238560.0,
      "end_time": 239839.0,
      "text": "respectable book."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 239839.0,
      "end_time": 241800.0,
      "text": "And throughout the 60s, paperback"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 241800.0,
      "end_time": 245159.0,
      "text": "publishers thought of education as El Dorado."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 245159.0,
      "end_time": 247800.0,
      "text": "El Dorado’s a mythical city of gold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 247800.0,
      "end_time": 249200.0,
      "text": "in case you forgot."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 249200.0,
      "end_time": 251240.0,
      "text": "Margins on mass-market paperbacks"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 251240.0,
      "end_time": 253480.0,
      "text": "were small, so publishers made money"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 253480.0,
      "end_time": 255540.0,
      "text": "by selling huge numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 255540.0,
      "end_time": 257940.0,
      "text": "Paperbacks sold a lot of copies worldwide."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 257940.0,
      "end_time": 259220.0,
      "text": "5 million."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 259540.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260440.00000000003,
      "text": "11 million."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 260600.00000000003,
      "end_time": 262340.0,
      "text": "And on and on and on."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 262340.0,
      "end_time": 264960.0,
      "text": "That’s why To Kill A Mockingbird is so famous."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 264960.0,
      "end_time": 268560.0,
      "text": "And you get the sense Harper knew it, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 268560.0,
      "end_time": 271300.0,
      "text": "When Lee died, her estate almost immediately"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 271300.0,
      "end_time": 273540.0,
      "text": "said they would discontinue the mass market"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 273540.0,
      "end_time": 274720.0,
      "text": "version of the book."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 274720.0,
      "end_time": 276620.0,
      "text": "Even if you think the paperback revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 276620.0,
      "end_time": 278040.0,
      "text": "made the book overrated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 278040.0,
      "end_time": 279840.0,
      "text": "it’s still kind of sad."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 280680.0,
      "end_time": 282620.0,
      "text": "These books, these cheap paperback,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 282620.0,
      "end_time": 285080.0,
      "text": "kinda hard to read mass-market books —"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 285080.0,
      "end_time": 286820.0,
      "text": "they're worth more than their price."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 287660.0,
      "end_time": 289200.0,
      "text": "Maybe they shouldn’t be killed."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 289200.0,
      "end_time": 291020.0,
      "text": "“Mockingbirds don’t do anything but"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 291020.0,
      "end_time": 293040.0,
      "text": "make music for us to enjoy."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 293860.0,
      "end_time": 295880.0,
      "text": "They don’t eat people’s gardens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 295880.0,
      "end_time": 298020.0,
      "text": "don’t nest in the corncribs."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 299000.0,
      "end_time": 301100.0,
      "text": "They don’t do one thing but just"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 301100.0,
      "end_time": 303360.0,
      "text": "sing their hearts out for us.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 307480.0,
      "end_time": 308960.0,
      "text": "This video is actually the first"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 308960.0,
      "end_time": 310320.0,
      "text": "in a series we're doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 310320.0,
      "end_time": 313000.0,
      "text": "about Overrated icons."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 313000.0,
      "end_time": 315020.0,
      "text": "You can look down below for"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 315040.0,
      "end_time": 316800.0,
      "text": "our Facebook page where we have more videos"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 316800.0,
      "end_time": 318320.0,
      "text": "and articles and"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 318320.0,
      "end_time": 320320.0,
      "text": "all sorts of other stuff about things that"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 320320.0,
      "end_time": 323020.0,
      "text": "might be just a little overrated."
    }
  ]
}